heroDescription:
A system that scores every incoming payment / account action in under 100 ms and decides: approve, review, or block. The hard parts:
      a <span class="hl">low-latency feature store</span> that can answer "how many card swipes has this user made in the last 5 minutes?" in &lt; 10 ms;
      an <span class="hl-accent">online ML model</span> co-located with features returning a risk score in single-digit milliseconds;
      and a <span class="hl-accent">feedback loop</span> that closes the gap between a human-confirmed chargeback (days later) and retraining the model, without letting the fraudsters get a week head-start.
      Stripe Radar, PayPal, Visa all run systems like this at 10K+ tx/sec.
